1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the power efficiency and achievable rates of a multi-pair relay channel, which is a topic of interest in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a communication system where multiple sources communicate with destinations using a relay, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper investigates the performance of a system with a very large antenna array, which can be analyzed using systems and control theory. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the achievable sum rate, which is a metric of interest in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves analyzing the power efficiency and achievable rates of a communication system, which can be considered a computational problem in engineering and science.
